# Website Deck Stacking Isolation

Applies when a website component uses intra-deck `zIndex` values on `position: absolute` slides with `transform` (e.g. `DECK_Z = [300, 200, 100, 50]`).

## Rule

1. **Scope deck depth inside the slider host.** The deck host `Box` (`position: relative`, parent of the absolute slide stack) MUST set `isolation: "isolate"` in `baseCssStyle` (or an equivalent scoped stacking context). Deck `zIndex` values order slides **only inside** that host.
2. **Do not compete with portaled overlays.** Authed shell drawers (`CustomerDrawer`, `CustomerDrawer`), visitor `LandingDrawer`, and modals use `zIndex.modals` (150) / `zIndex.modals + 1` (151) on `document.body`. Unscoped deck `zIndex` up to 300 paints above the drawer on mobile (reported defect on `/customer`).
3. **Prefer isolation over retuning `DECK_Z`.** Keep existing `DECK_Z` depth values when isolation fixes global stacking. Lowering `DECK_Z` to small integers is an acceptable alternative only when isolation is impossible.
4. **Do not raise drawer z-index** above arbitrary page content without auditing all overlays (`zIndex.loadable` 200, etc.).

## Canonical case

`CustomerHeroSlider` (`website/src/app/ui/components/customer/home/CustomerHeroSlider.tsx`) — deck host `Box`:

```tsx
baseCssStyle={{
    isolation: "isolate",
    overflow: "visible",
    // ...
}}
```

## Defects this prevents

- Customer drawer/backdrop visible **under** hero banner cards when opening the menu on mobile `/customer`.
- Future deck/banner sliders repeating the same global z-index leak over portaled UI.

